Dose-response curve of antitrypanosomal activity of Syzygium aromaticum essential oil and eugenol. Activity against epimastigotes (a) and intracellular amastigote of Trypanosoma cruzi (b) after 72 and 24 hours of treatment, respectively. Data represent mean ± standard deviation of the experiment realized in triplicate;
∗
p < 0.05 when compared by Mann–Whitney test.
